    Represents a unique string identifier of either a DynamicDefinition or specific DynamicDefinitionVersion. Can be converted from and to String.

    The following are examples of a definition id:

    • dataset:document - a document definition with key "document" in dataset with key "dataset"
    • dataset:views:name - a view with key "name" in dataset "dataset"
    • dataset:document/child - a child document (with key "child") of the document with key "document" in dataset with key "dataset"
    • dataset:document/views:name - a child view (with key "name") of the document with key "document" in dataset with key "dataset"
    In the examples above the id always refers to a DynamicDefinition. Optionally a version label can be added in which case the id refers to a DynamicDefinitionVersion instead. Examples:
    • dataset:document@1.0
    • dataset:views:name@1.0
    • dataset:document/child@1.0
